 a soap where people pull lambs out of sheep all day.</strong> O’Connor has already worked on EastEnders. Indeed, he has been criticised for bringing some of the TV soap’s breathless sensationalism to Ambridge.</p> <p><strong>I wouldn’t go that far.</strong> Perhaps you’re forgetting about all those dramatic storylines: the sudden deaths, the fights, the affairs, the bypass …</p> <p><strong>Not to mention the abuse Helen Titchener, née Archer, is currently suffering at the hands of that scumbag, Rob. </strong>Are you sure you’re not a loyal listener?</p> <p><strong>Don’t be ridiculous. Sometimes, when I visit my mum on Sundays </strong>… It’s nothing to be ashamed of – 4.8 million people regularly tune in.</p> <p><strong>So who is O’Connor’s replacement going to be?</strong> It’s not yet known, but whoever they choose will have to strike a difficult balance between maintaining ratings and satisfying the traditionalist fanbase.</p> <p><strong>Perhaps the new editor could organise a huge cake sale in a barn, and then burn the barn down? </strong>Your idea will be passed on to the relevant department.</p> <p><strong>Do say:</strong> “This job would be perfect for anyone with experience in radio drama, a deep knowledge of the show’s history and a real drive to innovate.”</p> <p><strong>Don’t say: </strong>“Except you, Helen darling. You need to rest.”</p>","internalOctopusCode":"11275051","productionOffice":"UK","newspaperEditionDate":"2016-02-22T00:00:00Z","hasStoryPackage":"false","internalPageCode":"2460145","internalRevision":"71","publication":"The Guardian","trailText":"Sean O’Connor is leaving Ambridge and heading east after a semi-controversial stint that brought death and chaos to rural Britain. Fancy his job?","allowUgc":"false","lang":"en","headline":"High drama in The Archers as editor leaves for Walford","isInappropriateForSponsorship":"false","commentable":"true","firstPublicationDate":"2016-02-21T17:30:33Z","secureThumbnail":"https://media.guim.co.uk/aa3d