ause he’s back with his ex-wife? </strong>Right, OK, yes. It has been reported that Phil Collins and Orianne Cevey have got back together, even though he is said to have paid her £25m in a divorce settlement nine years ago, and she got married to someone else and had a baby in the interim. </p> <p><strong>So what does that have to do with all this stuff about reincarnation? </strong>It’s linked, I promise. <a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-3429274/How-Phil-Collins-won-ex-wife-never-stopped-loving-d-married-man-d-paid-25m-divorce-money.html\">Reports</a> about the reunion suggest that – among other things – Phil’s obsession with the Alamo is what helped to drive Cevey away in the first place.</p> <p><strong>OK.</strong> And that in 2014, just as relations between the pair were starting to thaw, <a href=\"http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/100-million-phil-collins-alamo-collection-in-the-works-20141029\">he gave away most of his $100m Alamo collection to a museum in San Antonio, Texas</a>.</p> <p><strong>So Phil Collins has shed himself of Alamo paraphernalia in order to have a happy life with the woman he loves? </strong>I think that’s where we’ve gone with this.</p> <p><strong>And why are you bringing it back up? Because you want to remind him of an old obsession that may have helped to ruin his marriage? </strong>I never said that.</p> <p><strong>It is, though, isn’t it? You hate the idea of Phil Collins being happy. </strong>No, that’s not it! Just, you know, reincarnation is weird and it’s in the public interest to know if any pop stars have ever believed in anything that is slightly non-traditional, even if it’s completely benign.</p> <p><strong>No, it isn’t.</strong> No, you’re right, it isn’t. God, I’m a monster.</p> <p><strong>Do say:</strong> “You Can’t Hurry Love”.</p> <p><strong>Don’t say:</strong> “Doesn’t Anyone Stay Together Anymore”?</p>","internalOctopusCode":"11222780","productionOffice":"UK","newspaperEditionDate":"2016-02-04T0